Git:
- Tracks changes to code , with undo , revert , inspect and collaborate
- Full history stored locally 

SVN = subVersion = centralised version control - only one copy 
- Slow 
- Server outages
- Network needed
- Branch conflicts

VCS = version control system (GIT) - Distributed version control 
- fast 
- resilent to outages 
- working offline 
- fast branches / merging  

Git = take snapshot of the whole repo/file at that time 
- Shows whole new file with one line changed 
- USES key-value stores 
- if the content stays the same = git refuses the same object 
- Git is content address   not file-named based 

Files stored as: 
- Blobs= files         
- trees = directories    
- commits = commits 
